div.p:
(1) reduce from 75% to as low as 66% the required proportion of Israeli
                    dependence on short-term, indirect purchases of oil (Israel wants a 50% test; in
                    the tight market of 1979 it reached 53%);

(2) lower the price criterion (on Israel’s average oil import payments) from the
                    highest 10% of US oil imports to the highest 20% (Israel proposes the top
                    30%);
